cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CR

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - This is the most likely category as the paper is primarily focused on the architecture of the Internet and how individuals can join forces towards collective ventures. 

2. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper draws on the concept of Nash equilibrium and uses game theory to design and analyze institutional mechanisms. 

3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses broader applications in social organization beyond the market-based character of the Internet, which falls under the scope of social and information networks. 

4. cs.CY (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may touch upon security concerns related to incremental deployability in the Internet architecture. 

5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Similar to the previous category, the paper may discuss security concerns related to incremental deployability, which falls under the scope of cryptography and security.
